manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Top of the line masks for everyone The Defender Safety Level 3 Procedure Mask is a 510(k) cleared Procedure Mask. It is intended to protect both the patient and healthcare personnel from transfer of microorganisms, body fluids and particulate material. Made with high quality Polypropylene and Spandex; The Level 3 Masks are comfortable to wear and free from natural rubber latex. The Mask consists of a metal wire wrapped in polypropylene to provide a better fit around the user’s face. The proprietary melt blown and spunbonded layers consist of an electrostatic charge that deflects incoming particles and allows for both higher protection and improved breathability. It is the perfect combination of performance and comfort.

About this Mask: 510(k) Cleared: Achieved market clearance to legally distribute to the USA. 510(k) number: K210705 4-Ply Construction: The outer and inner layers are made of spunbond polypropylene to provide high breathability and comfort. The material is biocompatibile (tested against ISO 10993:5,10) and is ideal for sensitive users. The Filter Layer is a proprietary combination of spunbond and meltblown filter that can provide over 98% efficiency in PFE and BFE. Premium Ear Loops: Ear loops are made of Spandex and free from natural rubber Latex. With its soft finish and strong tensile strength, it provides unmatched comfort and fit for long periods of use. Strong Malleable Nose Wire: To conform to various types of face structures, the nose wire is made of iron wrapped in polypropylene to adjust to almost all face shapes and sizes.

Development and Manufacturing Process The Defender Safety Procedure and Surgical Mask Line were designed and tested in the USA. The development was compliant under FDA QSR 820 Design Control, and the testing was performed in an accredited ISO 17025 testing facility. Manufacturing took place in China. The Manufacturing Facility is compliant with cGMP, and ISO 13485:2016.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seem like very good quality.
reviews.reviewText: The reason I looked for better masks was when in my Dr's. office. the nurse quickly slipped a mask on me when I was showing an elevated temperature and I realized the the masks I had at home were very poor quality. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I've been wearing these masks at church, the grocery store, the gym, while getting my haircut, and anywhere else I need a mask for at least several months. Best mask I have found for regular use during the coronavirus pandemic. These masks are thick, but breathable. Ear loops are sturdy - have never had one break on me. The nose clip allows for a very good fit around my nose - if I get to talking too much with the mask on, it sometimes still slips down, but that is somewhat unavoidable with any mask. I'm not a medical professional, although my wife is an ICU nurse and even she has remarked how good these masks seem. Short of finding an actual N95 mask, it seems like you can't really ever be completely sure about the quality of a particular mask, but these masks really do seem like they provide a better degree of protection than cloth masks or other cheap disposable masks. I highly recommend these masks - I'll certainly be using them for the rest of the pandemic.
